The largest by-election window since the 2016 Local Government Elections is taking place across South Africa on Wednesday, according to the Independent Electoral Commission. A statement released by the IEC indicates that “the by-elections will be contested by hundred and five (105) candidates from fifteen (15) political parties and five (5) independent candidates.” The Municipal Structures Act of 1998 specifies that by-elections can occur in a number of permutations, namely:
• Whenever a councillor dies;
• resigns from the party;
• resigns from the council;
• is expelled from his/ her party or
• is expelled from the council The legislation also outlines that by-elections can occur when the IEC does not declare the results of an election or when a court sets aside the election of a council or ward and when a council is dissolved. !function(e,t,s,i){var n="InfogramEmbeds",o=e.getElementsByTagName("script")[0],d=/^http:/.test(e.location)?"http:":"https:";if(/^\/{2}/.test(i)&&(i=d+i),window[n]&&window[n].initialized)window[n].process&&window[n].process();else if(!e.getElementById(s)){var r=e.createElement("script");r.async=1,r.id=s,r.src=i,o.parentNode.insertBefore(r,o)}}(document,0,"infogram-async","https://e.infogram.com/js/dist/embed-loader-min.js");